pageContext.claim: “Boeing makes airplanes. They had a big problem with one, but they make the greatest airplanes. They make the best airplanes in the world. They had the problem with one. They got it too complex. It becomes so complex you have to be number one in your class at MIT to be able to fly it.”
pageContext.analysis: Boeing’s 737 Max was not grounded because it was “so complex” rather there were errors with the planes operating system that led to two crashes.
